Ecological notes : very common in all types of woodland; heath and parkland; wooded river bank; old hedges; sedge bed; water meadows; old sand and gravel workings; calcareous grassland; gardens. Reared from the fungi
Phaeolus schweinitzii
on pine and
Trametes versicolor
. iv–x.
